title: Daifuku Mochi
description: Classic Japanese red bean ice cream enhanced with sweetened anko and chopped red beans.

title: Sakura Mochi
description: An earthy sweetness from the red bean paste, balanced by the bright saltiness of the pickled sakura leaf.

title: Dango
description: Pink for cherry blossom, white the snow which has just melted to be spring and green for freshness of the greens in the spring season.

title: Mizu Shingen Mochi
description: A jelly-like dessert made only with mineral water and agar powder.

title: Strawberry Cheesecake Mochi
description: Soft and chewy. Stuffed with cream cheese, strawberry jam and topped with crushed biscuits.

title: Sakura Yokan
description: The perfect blend of a traditional snack that has been perfectly combined with the delicate sakura flavor.

title: Bunny Snowskin Mooncakes
description: The cute jade rabbits of the mooncake festival are also here to join in the fun.

title: Strawberry Yogurt Cream Mochi
description: Strawberry puree brings out the vibrant sweetness of the berries.

title: Cherry Blossom Macarons
description: Crunchy, soft and gooey almond shells with a tart, creamy, fluffly raspberry and jasmine chantilly cream.

title: Lemon Mochi
description: Upon opening the wrapper to this yellow mochi, the scent of lemon comes wafting out thanks to the setouchi lemon peels kneaded into the soft, chewy rice cake.
